        "title": "Infrastructure from Specs: spec-driven development for cloud solutions",
        "excerpt":"Specifications are becoming executable artifacts. How do modern Spec-Driven Development (SDD) frameworks invert traditional infrastructure workflows? Instead of writing code and hoping documentation keeps up, you write specifications that generate implementation.   Let‚Äôs compare two leading frameworks (Kiro Specs, GitHub SpecKit) and examine their approaches to capturing architectural intent, enforcing consistency across teams, and preventing infrastructure drift.   Whether you‚Äôre building greenfield systems or evolving existing cloud infrastructure, learn how to use specs as your single source of truth and why this matters at scale.  ","categories": [],
