        "title": "State of DevOps  (Our DORA ‚Äî not theirs)",
        "excerpt":"Since DevOps was born we‚Äôve had git, declarative pipelines, containers, serverless infrastructure, social coding and AI. Where does that leave DevOps today?   All though EU‚Äôs Digital Operational Resilience Act is getting a lot of attention these days. It‚Äôs not the DORA we‚Äôre referring to. In the DevOps community and culture, we have known DORA for more than 10 years now ‚Äî as something else.   Ours: DevOps Research and Assessment Institute (DORA) Theirs: Digital Operational Resilience Act (DORA)  ","categories": [],
